*** Installing LAMMPS ***

Detailed information on how to build LAMMPS can be found on the official
website (http://lammps.sandia.gov). Before building LAMMPS for ELBA, please
read the official LAMMPS compilation instructions. 

The following guidelines are guaranteed to work with the 28May12 version 
of LAMMPS, whereas they may or may not work with other versions. 

i) Pre-compilation

The following protocol assembles the ELBA-required source code and discards 
many non-necessary components:

- Download and extract LAMMPS tarball from official website 
- cd lammps-28May12/src/
- make no-all 
- make yes-dipole yes-molecule 
- cp USER-MISC/pair_dipole_sf.* .
- cp USER-MISC/angle_dipole.* .
- make yes-user-omp 

ii) Compilation

Compiling LAMMPS can be non-trivial, as compilation protocols tend to be 
system-specific. So you must have a "Makefile" which is suitable for your 
machine. The Makefiles provided in this directory, or those shipped with 
the official LAMMPS distribution, may work for you or may need adapting.
 
As examples, these are compilation protocols that work for me on computers 
running GNU/Linux operating systems:
 
*) Protocol to compile LAMMPS on the Hector HPC machine (Cray XE6):
- cp elba-lammps/install/Makefile.xe6 lammps-28May12/src/MAKE
- cd lammps-28May12/src
- module swap PrgEnv-cray PrgEnv-gnu 
- make xe6

*) Protocol to compile LAMMPS on the Iridis HPC machine (U Southampton):
- cp elba-lammps/install/Makefile.iridis-icc-fast lammps-28May12/src/MAKE
- cd lammps-28May12/src
- module load intel openmpi
- make iridis-icc-fast

*) Protocol to compile LAMMPS on a UOS desktop (U Southampton):
- cp elba-lammps/install/Makefile.uos-icc lammps-28May12/src/MAKE 
- cd lammps-28May12/src
- module load icc openmpi
- make uos-icc

Mario Orsi (orsimario@gmail.com)
